        public final void addWithDeferredIdAllocation​(FullEntity<?>... entities)
        Description copied from interface: DatastoreBatchWriter
        Datastore add operation. This method will also allocate id for any entity with an incomplete key. As opposed to DatastoreBatchWriter.add(FullEntity) and DatastoreBatchWriter.add(FullEntity...), this method will defer any necessary id allocation to submit time.

        addWithDeferredIdAllocation in interface DatastoreBatchWriter

        public final Entity add​(FullEntity<?> entity)
        Description copied from interface: DatastoreBatchWriter

If entity has a complete key and was already marked for deletion in this writer, the operation will be changed to DatastoreBatchWriter.put(com.google.cloud.datastore.FullEntity<?>).

        public final List<Entity> put​(FullEntity<?>... entities)
        Description copied from interface: DatastoreBatchWriter
